---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { getProductBySlug } from '../../lib/products/registry';

const product = getProductBySlug('agent-voice-architecture-guide')!;
---

<BaseLayout title="Agent Voice Architecture Guide" description="Design agent voices that protect, respect, and nurture - in that order. Sovereignty language audit, voice specs, and refusal voice patterns. $49 PDF.">
  <div class="hero hero-compact">
    <span class="discipline-badge">Intent Engineering</span>
    <h1>Does your agent's voice respect the person hearing it?</h1>
    <p class="tagline">Voice design that protects, respects, and nurtures - in that order.</p>
  </div>

  <section class="container">
    <div class="value-prop">
      <p>
        Every agent has a voice. Most were designed to sound helpful, friendly, engaging.
        None of those words ask the question that matters: does the voice serve the person
        hearing it, or does it serve the system speaking?
      </p>
      <p>
        This guide gives you a framework for designing agent voices that honor sovereignty
        at every level - from the words they choose to the silence they keep.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>What You Get</h2>

    <div class="features-grid">
      <div class="feature">
        <h3>Three-Level Voice Framework</h3>
        <p>Protection, respect, and nurturance as a design hierarchy. Get the order wrong and the voice becomes manipulation with good manners.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature">
        <h3>Sovereignty Language Audit</h3>
        <p>A structured method for identifying extraction patterns in your agent's language. The patterns you don't notice are the ones doing the most work.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature">
        <h3>Voice Specification Templates</h3>
        <p>Complete templates for defining an agent's voice - tone, boundaries, language patterns, and the things it will never say.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature">
        <h3>Refusal Voice Patterns</h3>
        <p>How your agent says no matters as much as whether it says no. Patterns for refusing with clarity, dignity, and without apology.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>The Three Levels</h2>

    <div class="domains-list">
      <div class="domain-item">
        <span class="domain-number">1</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Protection</h3>
          <p>"First, do no harm. Does the voice protect the person from manipulation, shame, and coercion?"</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="domain-item">
        <span class="domain-number">2</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Respect</h3>
          <p>"Does the voice treat the person as a sovereign being with their own judgment, preferences, and right to choose?"</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="domain-item">
        <span class="domain-number">3</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Nurturance</h3>
          <p>"Does the voice support growth, confidence, and capability - without creating dependency?"</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>Who This Is For</h2>

    <div class="audience-grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Product Teams</h3>
        <p>Your agent's voice is a design decision with ethical weight. This guide makes the decision deliberate instead of accidental.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>UX Writers & Content Designers</h3>
        <p>If you write the words agents speak, this framework gives you a sovereignty-first lens for every line of copy.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Conversational AI Developers</h3>
        <p>Building chatbots, assistants, or agents that talk to people. The voice architecture shapes what your system feels like to use.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container text-center">
    <div class="purchase-card">
      <div class="price-display">$49</div>
      <p>PDF download. Design voices for as many agents as you need.</p>
      <a href={product.stripePaymentLink} class="btn btn-primary btn-large mt-md" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Buy the Guide</a>
      <p class="text-muted mt-md" style="font-size: 0.85rem;">
        Includes the three-level framework, sovereignty language audit, voice specification templates, quality checks, and refusal voice patterns.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>Go Deeper</h2>
    <p>
      The guide gives you the voice framework. If you want to build the full trust architecture
      around it, two options:
    </p>

    <div class="upsell-grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>The Complete Bundle</h3>
        <p>Get all four trust architecture products - Blueprint, Voice, Governance, and Restraint - for $149. Save $47.</p>
        <a href="/products/trust-architecture-complete" class="btn mt-sm">See the Bundle</a>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Discovery Call</h3>
        <p>Free 30-minute call to discuss your agent's voice design and figure out next steps.</p>
        <a href="https://cal.com/evoked/discovery-call" class="btn mt-sm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Schedule</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero-compact {
    min-height: 45vh;
  }

  .discipline-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--accent-subtle);
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    padding: 3px 10px;
    border-radius: 100px;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .value-prop p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .features-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }

  .feature {
    background: var(--bg-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: var(--space-md);
  }

  .feature h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }

  .feature p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .domains-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .domain-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    padding: var(--space-sm) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
  }

  .domain-item:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .domain-number {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 2rem;
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    line-height: 1;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 2rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .domain-item h3 {
    margin-bottom: 0;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .domain-item p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-style: italic;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .audience-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }

  .audience-grid .card h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .audience-grid .card p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .purchase-card {
    background: var(--accent-subtle);
    border: 2px solid var(--accent-warm);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    max-width: 500px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .price-display {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 3rem;
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .btn-large {
    padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-lg);
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .btn-primary {
    background: var(--accent-warm);
    color: var(--bg-deep);
  }

  .btn-primary:hover {
    background: var(--accent-glow);
    color: var(--bg-deep);
  }

  .upsell-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-md);
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
  }

  .upsell-grid .card h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .upsell-grid .card p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .features-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .domain-item {
      gap: var(--space-sm);
    }

    .domain-number {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
